                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3052438831"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "i think what @echasnovski was suggesting is to add a `__eq` metamethod here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7a27c5b0c88097e65d2ac677ec17b075271b689f/runtime/lua/vim/version.lua#L274\n\nfor reference here's `__eq` for `vim.Version`: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7a27c5b0c88097e65d2ac677ec17b075271b689f/runtime/lua/vim/version.lua#L121\n\nNote: it probably doesn't make sense for `__lt` or `__gt`, so don't bother with that...",
            "commit_id": "fb11ec4b5e2b795cd88b94e4f7c18603a591b9c0",
            "created_at": "2026-04-08T15:31:57Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -957,6 +957,13 @@ local function lock_read(confirm, specs)\n   lock_sync(vim.F.if_nil(confirm, true), vim.F.if_nil(specs, {}))\n end\n \n+local function version_spec_equal(v1, v2)",
