    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think it should be `feat(vim.version)` and not `fix(pack)`. This change is valuable on its own, while the latter comes as a side effect.\r\n\r\n> would you mind adding a test here:\r\n\r\nI think it should be the only new test. The proposed `vim.pack` test case feels too niche compared to how much complexity it adds. But if @justinmk has another opinion, then at least inlining `chmod_lock_path` helper inside a test case seems better.",
